<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n08171i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08171i">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08171i"> 171(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ no Peter&apos;s pence</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The Irish Church, which had obtained such glowing fame in its early days, had long since &hellip; grown into very bad repute with Rome. &hellip; tithes and firstfruits were not collected with any regularity; above all, the collection of Peter&apos;s pence, being the sum of one penny due from every household, was always scandalously in arrears, nay, often no attempt was made to collect it at all. <small> Emily Lawless, <a name="ELIS" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ELIS"><cite title="source">Ireland (Story of Nations series</cite></a> (192?) 79</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c03031i" href="c03all.htm#c03031i">VI.C.03:031(i)</a></mm></dd> </dd></dl>
